The article is a transcript of a speech delivered by Vice President Mike Pence at the Council for National Policy. Pence expressed gratitude for the support he has received over the past four years and pledged to continue fighting for a fair and legal election. He highlighted the accomplishments of the Trump administration, including rebuilding the military, reviving the economy, appointing conservative judges, and standing for the sanctity of life. Pence emphasized the importance of protecting the integrity of the vote and preventing the Democrats from implementing their agenda, which he believes would lead to American decline. He urged the audience to stay in the fight for freedom and have faith in the future.